  "response_text": "Sure! Here’s a healthy grocery list that includes a variety of nutritious foods suitable for both a mother and a 2-year-old. This list focuses on whole foods that are rich in vitamins, minerals, and other essential nutrients.\n\n### Fruits\n- Bananas\n- Apples (sliced for easy eating)\n- Berries (strawberries, blueberries, or raspberries)\n- Oranges or mandarins\n- Avocados\n\n### Vegetables\n- Spinach or kale (great for smoothies and salads)\n- Carrots (baby carrots or cut into sticks for easy snacking)\n- Broccoli (steamed or raw)\n- Sweet potatoes (easy to bake or mash)\n- Bell peppers (sliced for dipping)\n\n### Whole Grains\n- Oatmeal (plain or flavored with fruit)\n- Whole grain bread or tortillas\n- Brown rice or quinoa\n- Whole grain pasta\n\n### Proteins\n- Chicken breast or thighs (skinless)\n- Lean ground turkey or beef\n- Eggs (great for breakfast or snacks)\n- Canned beans (black beans, chickpeas)\n- Greek yogurt (plain or with fruit)\n\n### Dairy or Dairy Alternatives\n- Milk (cow's milk or fortified plant-based milk)\n- Cheese (cheddar, mozzarella, or string cheese)\n- Cottage cheese\n\n### Healthy Fats\n- Nut butters (peanut, almond, or sunflower seed butter)\n- Olive oil or avocado oil (for cooking)\n\n### Snacks\n- Hummus (great with veggies or whole grain pita)\n- Whole grain crackers\n- Popcorn (plain or lightly salted)\n- Dried fruit (without added sugar)\n\n### Beverages\n- Water (consider a fun water bottle for the toddler)\n- Herbal teas (caffeine-free options for mom)\n\n### Optional\n- Spices and herbs (to flavor meals without added salt)\n- Low-sugar cereals (for quick breakfasts)\n\n### Tips\n- Focus on fresh, seasonal produce for best flavor and nutrition.\n- Choose organic options when possible, especially for produce with high pesticide residues.\n- Look for low-sodium options for canned goods, and rinse beans before using to reduce sodium.\n\nThis list provides a good balance of macronutrients and essential vitamins and minerals that both a mother and a toddler need. Adjust quantities based on your family's preferences and dietary needs. Happy shopping!",
